          + Tutorials
     * Contributing

2D

     * [https://www.assetstore.unity3d.com/en/#!/content/17722]2D Rope
       System (Paid) - Scripts for creating any type of 2D ropes in the
       editor or during runtime.
     * [https://www.assetstore.unity3d.com/en/#!/content/908]2D Toolkit
       (Paid) - An efficient & flexible 2D sprite, collider set-up, text,
       tilemap and UI system.
     * [https://www.assetstore.unity3d.com/en/#!/content/11653]Ferr2D
       Terrain Tool (Paid) - Quickly create handcrafted 2D landscapes and
       levels.
     * [https://github.com/RyanNielson/PixelCamera2D]Pixel Camera 2D - A
       simple pixel perfect camera with scaling options for 2D Games.
     * [http://esotericsoftware.com/]Spine (Paid) - A skeletal animation
       editor with a Unity library.
     * [http://www.seanba.com/tiled2unity]Tiled2Unity - Takes your
       [http://www.mapeditor.org/]Tiled files and creates Unity prefabs
       from them that are easily placed into your Unity scene. Complex
       collision is supported through Unity's PolygonCollider2D class.
     * [https://www.assetstore.unity3d.com/en/#!/content/79840]Unity
       Anima2D - Advanced skeletal animation editor with support for both
       per-object and skinned mesh animation with an integrated in-editor
       skinning tool.
     * [https://github.com/nickgravelyn/UnityTiled]UnityTiled - An
       importer for [http://www.mapeditor.org/]Tiled maps.

AI

     * [http://arongranberg.com/astar/]A* Pathfinding Project - Lightning
       fast pathfinding with heavily optimized algorithms and a large
       feature set.
     * [https://www.assetstore.unity3d.com/en/#!/content/17943]Apex Path
       (Paid) - Apex Path handles dynamic pathfinding including local
       avoidance steering and dynamic obstacles.
     * [https://github.com/igiagkiozis/CrystalAI]Crystal AI - Crystal is a
       fast, scalable and extensible utility based AI framework for C# and
       Unity.

Augmented & Virtual Reality

     * [http://artoolkit.org/documentation/doku.php?id=6_Unity:unity_about
       ]ARToolKit - Augmented Reality SDK that includes libraries,
       utilities, and examples.
     * [https://developers.google.com/vr/unity]Google VR SDK - Scripts and
       prefabs to help with the development of Google Daydream and
       Cardboard apps for Android and iOS.
     * [https://www.assetstore.unity3d.com/en/#!/content/64131]SteamVR
       Unity Toolkit - Scripts and Great examples to abstract the use of
       VR controller actions in Unity.
     * [https://vuforia.com/]Vuforia - Augmented Reality SDK with image
       and object recognition, smart terrain and extended tracking
       features.

Camera

     * [https://www.assetstore.unity3d.com/en/#!/content/2943]UFPS (Paid)
       - Provides camera, controllers, and other effects for use in FPS
       games.

Character Controllers

     * [https://github.com/prime31/CharacterController2D]CharacterControll
       er2D - A 2D controller that behaves very similarly to Unity's
       CharacterController component.

Frameworks

     * [https://github.com/snozbot/fungus]Fungus - An easy to use Unity 3D
       library for creating illustrated Interactive Fiction games.
     * [http://strangeioc.github.io/strangeioc/]StrangeIoC - Strange is a
       super-lightweight and highly extensible Inversion-of-Control (IoC)
       framework, written specifically for C# and Unity.
     * [https://www.assetstore.unity3d.com/en/#!/content/14381]uFrame
       (Paid) - Create maintainable games faster, better, more stable, and
       consistent than ever before.

Input

     * [https://github.com/pbhogan/InControl]InControl - An input manager
       that tames makes handler cross-platform. controller input easy.
     * [https://github.com/RyanNielson/InputBinder]InputBinder - Bind game
       inputs to methods via code or using the inspector to add event
       driven input handling to your project.
     * [https://github.com/prime31/TouchKit]TouchKit - Makes it easy to
       recognize gestures and other touch input.
     * [https://github.com/TouchScript/TouchScript]TouchScript - Makes
       handling complex gesture interactions on any touch surface much
       easier.

Modeling

     * [https://www.assetstore.unity3d.com/en/#!/content/11919]Prototype -
       Uses the core of ProBuilder, enabling you to build entire game
       levels (or objects) with speed and simplicity.
     * [http://sabrecsg.com/]SabreCSG - A set of
       [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constructive_solid_geometry]CSG
       level design tools for building complex levels quickly inside
       Unity.

Monetization

     * [https://www.assetstore.unity3d.com/en/#!/content/21027]Unity Ads -
       Unity Ads is a video ad network with quick and seamless integration
       using regular and opt-in ads.

Networking

     * [https://www.assetstore.unity3d.com/en/#!/content/81338]Nakama -
       Build social and realtime games with an open-source
       [https://github.com/heroiclabs/nakama]distributed server.
     * [https://www.assetstore.unity3d.com/en/#!/content/41330]Photon Bolt
       (Paid) - Build networked games without having to know the details
       of networking or write any complex networking code.
     * [https://www.assetstore.unity3d.com/en/#!/content/1786]Photon Unity
       Networking - Plug and play cloud networking that also works for
       local hosting. Free for up to 20 concurrent users.

Scripting

     * [https://www.assetstore.unity3d.com/en/#!/content/768]Easy Save 2
       (Paid) - A fast and simple way to save and load data on all major
       platforms supported by Unity.
     * [https://www.assetstore.unity3d.com/en/#!/content/10070]Mad Level
       Manager (Paid) - Provides a level manager, level selector, and
       progress save/load tools to make it easy to transition between
       levels and make level selection screens.
     * [https://www.assetstore.unity3d.com/en/#!/content/2714]UniStorm
       (Paid) - A customizable dynamic day and night weather system that
       creates realistic storms and weather.

Services

     * [https://www.assetstore.unity3d.com/en/#!/content/28120]Unity
       Analytics - Provides a dashboard with metrics to help track active
       players, sessions, retention, and revenue.

Shaders

     * [https://www.assetstore.unity3d.com/en/#!/content/14147]Shader
       Forge (Paid) - A node-based shader editor giving you the artistic
       freedom of shader creation, with no need to code.

Textures

     * [https://www.assetstore.unity3d.com/en/#!/content/7940]8 Free
       Substances (Free) - 8 configurable procedural textures.

Tweening

     * [https://www.assetstore.unity3d.com/en/#!/content/27676]DOTween -
       Tween any numeric property or field (including Vectors, Rectangles,
       etc.), plus some non-numeric ones (like strings). This is the
       follow-up to HOTween.
     * [https://www.assetstore.unity3d.com/en/#!/content/3663]GoKit - An
       open source, lightweight tween library aimed at making tweening
       objects dead simple.
     * [https://www.assetstore.unity3d.com/en/#!/content/84]iTween - A
       simple, and easy to use animation system.
     * [https://www.assetstore.unity3d.com/en/#!/content/3595]LeanTween -
       FOSS, and also the most lightweight tweening library for Unity.
       Allows you to tween any value you have access to via the .value()
       method.

UI

     * [https://www.assetstore.unity3d.com/en/#!/content/2413]NGUI (Paid)
       - A powerful UI system and event notification framework.
     * [https://www.assetstore.unity3d.com/en/#!/content/84126]TextMesh
       Pro - A alternative to render text in uGUI by using the distance
       field technique, which allows crisp fonts at any scale. This was
       recently purchased by Unity and will be integrated into the engine
       in the future.

Utilities

     * [https://github.com/mminer/consolation]Consolation - In-game debug
       console that displays output from Debug.Log.
     * [https://www.assetstore.unity3d.com/en/#!/content/20232]CSharpatron
       (Paid) - Automatically convert scripts from UnityScript to C#
       without breaking existing game objects.
     * [https://unity.github.com/]GitHub for Unity - The new GitHub for
       Unity extension brings the GitHub workflow and more to Unity,
       providing support for large files with Git LFS and file locking.
     * [https://github.com/mminer/scene-view-bookmarks]Scene View
       Bookmarks - Editor extension to bookmark and later recall scene
       views.
     * [https://www.assetstore.unity3d.com/en/#!/content/19245]SnazzyGrid
       (Paid) - Makes it easy to manage positions of assets in the scene
       with easy to use snapping tools and many more features to improve
       the scene creation workflow.
     * [https://www.assetstore.unity3d.com/en/#!/content/9733]UniMerge
       (Paid) - Editor extension for merging scenes and prefabs, also
       integrates with VCS.
     * [https://github.com/neuecc/UniRx]UniRx - UniRx (Reactive Extensions
       for Unity) is a reimplementation of the .NET Reactive Extensions.
       Rx cures the "asynchronous blues" without async/await.
     * [https://github.com/nickgravelyn/unitytoolbag]UnityToolbag -
       Collection of miscellaneous open source scripts and helpers for
       Unity 5.0.

Visual Scripting

     * [https://www.assetstore.unity3d.com/en/#!/content/368]Playmaker
       (Paid) - Quickly make gameplay prototypes, A.I. behaviors,
       animation graphs, interactive objects, and more using finite state
       machines.

Projects

Games

     * [https://github.com/Hyperparticle/nodulus]Nodulus - A complete
       puzzle game with a clever twist. Play it online.

Resources

Tips and Tricks

     * [http://imgur.com/a/2w7zd]Editor Tips - Tips in gif form showing a
       few ways to use the editor more efficiently.
     * [https://unity3d.com/learn/tutorials/topics/tips]Unity Tips - Short
       videos showing some handy tips when using Unity.

Tutorials

     * [http://nielson.io/2015/12/splatter-effects-in-unity-using-the-sten
       cil-buffer]2D Splatter Effects Using the Stencil Buffer - Using the
       stencil buffer in Unity to draw splatter effects on surfaces. This
       could be used for paint or blood splatter.
     * [http://www.alanzucconi.com/2015/06/10/a-gentle-introduction-to-sha
       ders-in-unity3d]A Gentle Introduction to Shaders in Unity3D - This
       series of posts will introduce you to shader coding, and is
       oriented to developers with little to no knowledge about shaders.
     * [http://www-cs-students.stanford.edu/%7Eamitp/gameprog.html]Amit's
       Game Programming Information - An great collection of general
       purpose game programming content.
     * [http://catlikecoding.com/unity/tutorials/]Catlike Coding -
       Tutorials designed for learning the C# scripting side of Unity.
     * [http://nielson.io/2015/10/fixing-gaps-between-sprites-better-2d-in
       -unity-part-2]Fixing Gaps Between Sprites - A short tutorial about
       removing the small gaps that sometimes appear between adjacent
       sprites.
     * [http://gameprogrammingpatterns.com/contents.html]Game Programming
       Patterns - Lots of great game development patterns useful when
       making games with or without Unity.
     * [https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLt_Y3Hw1v3QTEbh8fQV1DUOUIh9
       nF0k6c]Modern GUI Development in Unity 4.6 - A video tutorial
       providing an in-depth explanation of Unity's new UI system.
     * [http://unity3d.com/learn/tutorials/modules]Official Video
       Tutorials - The official tutorials for scripting, animation, audio,
       and almost anything Unity related.
     * [http://www.raywenderlich.com/category/unity]Ray Wenderlich's
       Tutorials - Beginner and mid-level tutorials focused on learning
       Unity features or creating small example games.
     * [https://developer.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/holographic/unity_de
       velopment_overview]Unity in HoloLens - Official tutorials from
       Microsoft for creating Microsoft HoloLens applications.
     * [http://docs.unity3d.com/Manual/VROverview.html]Unity Virtual
       Reality - Unity's official documentation on developing virtual
       reality applications.

